{
  "texts": [
    "Subsequently, Merk et al.",
    "(Merk et al., 2018a), trained a GAI model on natural products to produce de novo ligands, and the resulting molecules were empirically verified as new retinoid X receptor (RXR) modulators.",
    "In another scientific breakthrough, to combat fibrosis, Hongkong/New York-based Insilico Medicine developed a GAI model GENTRL (Generative Tensorial Reinforcement Learning) to identify novel kinase DDR1 inhibitors.",
    "They performed biological tests to confirm the efficacy of the GENTRL-generated compounds.",
    "Their research stood out because they went from insilico to a successful preclinical phase in only 21 days, an achievement that had never been accomplished before (Zhavoronkov et al., 2019)."
  ]
}